  "overview": {
    "value": "Wallops Flight Facility is a rocket launch site on Wallops Island on the Eastern Shore of Virginia, United States. The facility is operated by the Goddard Space Flight Center in Greenbelt, Maryland, and primarily serves to support science and exploration missions for NASA and other federal agencies. It includes a range that supports launches of sounding rockets, small expendable suborbital and orbital rockets, and high-altitude balloon flights.",
